                            <comment id="12999265" author="lars t" created="Fri, 25 Feb 2011 08:37:49 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Since I&apos;m extracting text only, is it possible to adapt your patch against the method prepareFontMetric?&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Or is invoking prepareFontMetric for text extraction required?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13000447" author="lehmi" created="Mon, 28 Feb 2011 18:21:19 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;@Lars&lt;br/&gt;
Good idea, thanks for the pointer. I created a new issue (&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/PDFBOX-967&quot; title=&quot;Create Type1C font metrics only when necessary&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;PDFBOX-967&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;PDFBOX-967&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;), moved your attachment to it and already submitted a patch.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13011783" author="lehmi" created="Sun, 27 Mar 2011 11:58:02 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Kevins patch was only half the battle. The type1 font constructor called the getawtFont method right after initializing the type1C font. I moved that call to the getawtFont of the type1 font, so that the AWTFont will only be created if needed.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
